### 2. Route Definitions & Organization

**Base URL:** `http://localhost:3001`

**Root Routes:**
- `GET /` → `{ success: true, data: { message: "Rearden API" } }`
- `GET /health` → `{ success: true, data: { status: "ok", timestamp: "..." } }`

**API Routes:** All prefixed with `/api/`

#### `/api/candidates`
- `GET /` - Fetch all candidates (in-memory array)
- `GET /:id` - Fetch candidate by ID (404 if not found)
- `POST /` - Create new candidate (generates UUID, timestamps)
  - Body: Partial Candidate object, merged with defaults
  - Returns: 201 Created with full Candidate object

#### `/api/search`
- `POST /` - Search candidates with scoring algorithm
  - Body: `{ query: string, filters?: SearchFilters }`
  - Returns: Results with scored candidates + metadata
  - Features:
    - 500ms artificial delay (for UX)
    - Token-based matching (skills, title, location, bio)
    - Experience level keywords (senior, junior, lead)
    - Normalized score 0-100
    - Filterable by: skills, location, experience range, availability

#### `/api/upload`
- `POST /` - Upload file to disk
  - Multipart form-data with `file` field
  - Returns: `{ url: "/api/upload/{filename}", filename }`
  - Stores in `./uploads/` with timestamp-UUID naming

- `GET /:filename` - Serve uploaded file
  - Content-Type detection (pdf, images, video, office)
  - 404 if file not found

